biz.sudden.designCoordination.handleBO.dataStructures
Class AbstractSupplyNetwork

java.lang.Object
  biz.sudden.designCoordination.handleBO.dataStructures.AbstractSupplyNetwork
All Implemented Interfaces:
Connectable
public class AbstractSupplyNetwork
extends java.lang.Object
implements Connectable

The 'infamous' abstract supply network. It's basically a team for which no team members have yet been assigned. Thus - at the minimum - it's a set of roles which normally have evaluation criteria attached to them (during HBO.). This last factor ISN'T guaranteed if the ASN has been produced by bottom up team formation. However the design is very general and the node structure can also contain some other information.

getInitialNode

@Deprecated
public ASNInitialNode getInitialNode()
Deprecated. 

Deprecated in order to handle Persistence use: public void addInitialNode(AbstractSupplyNetwork asn, ASNInitialNode initialNode) and similar in HanleBOService

Returns:
See Also:
Get the initial node. This method shouldn't ever fail for a well constructed ASN, although the actual initial node can contain no information. If it does It will return a null answer. Note that this node is only 'initial' in the sense of the subchain of suppliers and material dependencies. The ASN itself has no real concept of direction.

recursivelyDeleteRoleNodeAndChildren

public void recursivelyDeleteRoleNodeAndChildren(ASNRoleNode nodeToDelete)
A recursive method for deleting role nodes - it deletes the role node along with every thing 'above' it in the Abstract supply networks graph. It is "above" because the ASN is a tree where the final product is the root.
